  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 7 for SLE 15 SP3)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 5.3.18-59_27 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2021-4202: Fixed NFC race condition by adding NCI_UNREG flag (bsc#1194533).\n- CVE-2022-0435: Fixed remote stack overflow in net/tipc module that validate domain record count on input (bsc#1195308).\n- CVE-2021-4083: Fixed a read-after-free memory flaw inside the garbage collection for Unix domain socket file handlers when users call close() and fget() simultaneouslyand can potentially trigger a race condition (bnc#1194460).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
